1
00:00:01,251 --> 00:00:02,169
[Mouse squeaks]

2
00:00:02,169 --> 00:00:03,796
[Penguins chirp]

3
00:00:04,838 --> 00:00:05,756
[Screeches]

4
00:00:05,839 --> 00:00:08,008
[All cheering]

5
00:00:10,052 --> 00:00:11,011
[Screeches]

6
00:00:11,053 --> 00:00:12,554
[Quacks]

7
00:00:13,180 --> 00:00:14,264
J "Adventure Time" J

8
00:00:14,306 --> 00:00:15,682
s Come on, grab your friends 7

9
00:00:15,766 --> 00:00:18,352
J We're going to
very distant lands J

10
00:00:18,393 --> 00:00:20,646
J With Jake the dog
and Finn the human &

11
00:00:20,771 --> 00:00:22,272
J The fun will never end J

12
00:00:22,272 --> 00:00:24,107
J It's "Adventure Time"“ J

13
00:00:32,792 --> 00:00:35,294
[Chatter, laughter, dinging]

14
00:00:44,470 --> 00:00:46,430
Birthday boy-e-e-e!

15
00:00:46,472 --> 00:00:48,057
Enjoying your party?

16
00:00:48,099 --> 00:00:50,559
It's great having fun
with all my friends.

17
00:00:50,601 --> 00:00:53,729
Well, some of my friends,
mostly banana guards.

18
00:00:53,813 --> 00:00:56,107
Yeah, sorry about that.

19
00:00:56,190 --> 00:00:58,109
The Candy Kingdom
is in full lockdown

20
00:00:58,192 --> 00:01:01,320
until I can sort out the rumors
about my Uncle Gumbald.

21
00:01:01,362 --> 00:01:04,907
He's been gone for years,
but we should stay vigilant.

22
00:01:04,949 --> 00:01:06,200
Don't worry, Pb.

23
00:01:06,325 --> 00:01:09,578
Now that I'm 17,
I'm feelin' ready for anything.

24
00:01:09,662 --> 00:01:12,081
Feels like I'm really
hitting my stride, y'know?

25
00:01:12,164 --> 00:01:14,208
MARCELINE: Finn, I want to give
you your gift before I forget.

26
00:01:14,333 --> 00:01:15,918
It's a harmonica.

27
00:01:17,461 --> 00:01:18,587
Awesome!

28
00:01:18,587 --> 00:01:19,922
[Inhales sharply]

29
00:01:20,464 --> 00:01:23,718
Finn, I designed
an exciting new game for you.

30
00:01:23,718 --> 00:01:24,593
Show me.

31
00:01:24,677 --> 00:01:27,221
It's called
"Birthday Boyfighter."

32
00:01:27,304 --> 00:01:29,223
[Game music plays]

33
00:01:30,850 --> 00:01:32,601
Looks like another hit.

34
00:01:32,601 --> 00:01:35,354
STARCHY: Finn, Starchy
didn't get you squat.

35
00:01:35,438 --> 00:01:37,106
I got you a present, too.

36
00:01:37,189 --> 00:01:40,609
It has emotional
and metaphorical significance.

37
00:01:40,693 --> 00:01:42,862
It's beautifully wrapped.

38
00:01:42,945 --> 00:01:43,988
Wonder what it is.

39
00:01:44,071 --> 00:01:45,573
It's an elk's heart.

40
00:01:45,614 --> 00:01:47,950
Oh, cool.
I don't have one of those.

41
00:01:47,992 --> 00:01:50,578
[Thumping]

42
00:01:50,619 --> 00:01:51,579
What's that sound?

43
00:01:51,620 --> 00:01:53,706
STARCHY:
It's zombies.

44
00:01:53,748 --> 00:01:55,249
HUNTRESS WIZARD:
Sounds like hooves.

45
00:01:55,374 --> 00:01:57,626
-[Galloping intensifies]
- STARCHY: Zombie cows.

46
00:02:00,379 --> 00:02:01,464
You're
green
|

47
00:02:01,505 --> 00:02:04,008
I'm the Green Knight!

48
00:02:04,091 --> 00:02:06,635
And before you ask,
yes, of course,

49
00:02:06,635 --> 00:02:08,554
I brought you
a birthday present.

50
00:02:09,430 --> 00:02:10,806
It's a battle axe.

51
00:02:10,890 --> 00:02:12,433
That's some axe.

52
00:02:12,558 --> 00:02:14,560
Am I an axe guy, though?

53
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:16,687
I've always thought of myself
as a sword guy.

54
00:02:16,771 --> 00:02:19,315
GREEN KNIGHT: But only if you
play me a game for it.

55
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:20,775
What's the game?

56
00:02:20,816 --> 00:02:23,903
GREEN KNIGHT: Oh, this game
is called "All you have to do

57
00:02:23,944 --> 00:02:26,947
is strike me with it,
and it is yours."

58
00:02:27,448 --> 00:02:28,074
Mm?

59
00:02:28,157 --> 00:02:30,201
[All murmuring]

60
00:02:30,284 --> 00:02:31,702
[Inhales sharply]

61
00:02:31,827 --> 00:02:34,538
I can't axe some stranger.

62
00:02:34,580 --> 00:02:36,290
Wait a minute!
Where's Jake?

63
00:02:38,667 --> 00:02:40,211
I know what's going on.

64
00:02:40,294 --> 00:02:42,797
No, I don't think you do.

65
00:02:42,838 --> 00:02:44,423
Relax, Princess.

66
00:02:44,465 --> 00:02:46,592
Jake loves playing
birthday pranks on me.

67
00:02:46,675 --> 00:02:49,970
Yes, of course,
one of Jake's classic pranks.

68
00:02:49,970 --> 00:02:52,348
Okay, I'm in.

69
00:02:54,558 --> 00:02:55,601
[Clank]

70
00:02:57,186 --> 00:02:58,854
May your aim be steady.

71
00:02:58,979 --> 00:03:01,482
[Laughs]
Sure thing...Jake!

72
00:03:03,734 --> 00:03:04,985
[Clank]

73
00:03:06,737 --> 00:03:09,198
- I win!
-[Cheers and applause]

74
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:11,200
- Yeah, Finn!
- Yeah, Finn!

75
00:03:13,244 --> 00:03:14,495
JAKE:
Happy birthday, Finn.

76
00:03:15,746 --> 00:03:16,997
-[Scary music plays]
-[Shrieks]

77
00:03:16,997 --> 00:03:19,875
Jake! When did you --
Whose head did I --

78
00:03:20,584 --> 00:03:21,836
Are you pranking me?

79
00:03:21,877 --> 00:03:23,504
What? No.

80
00:03:23,587 --> 00:03:25,131
My prank is this fake-out gift.

81
00:03:27,466 --> 00:03:28,259
Huh?

82
00:03:30,886 --> 00:03:32,638
What's this guy's deal?

83
00:03:33,722 --> 00:03:35,224
Oh, nuh-uh!

84
00:03:35,266 --> 00:03:37,101
Banana guards, surround him!

85
00:03:37,143 --> 00:03:40,104
And be on the lookout
for anything else strange!

86
00:03:40,146 --> 00:03:41,272
BANANA GUARDS:
Hup, hup, hup, hup!

87
00:03:41,355 --> 00:03:42,648
Surrender, please.

88
00:03:45,359 --> 00:03:47,027
Princess, is that strange?

89
00:03:47,027 --> 00:03:48,028
Yes!

90
00:03:48,028 --> 00:03:49,405
I did good.

91
00:03:49,488 --> 00:03:50,865
[Screaming]

92
00:03:53,909 --> 00:03:55,286
My guards!

93
00:03:55,411 --> 00:03:57,413
- I got this.
-[Shing!]

94
00:03:57,496 --> 00:03:58,914
Raaahh!!

95
00:03:58,998 --> 00:04:00,166
[Hisses]

96
00:04:01,917 --> 00:04:03,252
Eell

97
00:04:07,173 --> 00:04:07,798
[Shing!]

98
00:04:10,301 --> 00:04:11,677
Get him!

99
00:04:12,553 --> 00:04:14,513
[Vells]

100
00:04:14,555 --> 00:04:15,806
[Groans]

101
00:04:16,765 --> 00:04:17,516
Aw.

102
00:04:19,643 --> 00:04:21,645
He might have
an invisible shield.

103
00:04:21,770 --> 00:04:24,023
But I'm not sure,
because it's invisible.

104
00:04:26,859 --> 00:04:27,401
Owiee.

105
00:04:27,526 --> 00:04:30,112
Yes.
It's an invisible shield.

106
00:04:30,154 --> 00:04:32,156
An invisible shield.

107
00:04:32,239 --> 00:04:33,908
I've got a device
for the dissolution

108
00:04:34,033 --> 00:04:35,534
of invisible shields.

109
00:04:35,618 --> 00:04:37,369
[Whirring, beeping]

110
00:04:39,371 --> 00:04:40,789
[Fizzles]

111
00:04:40,915 --> 00:04:42,124
Impossible.

112
00:04:42,166 --> 00:04:44,293
[Laughs maniacally]
Heh!

113
00:04:44,376 --> 00:04:45,794
Back off, everyone.

114
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:48,005
He's using some advanced
mystery tech.

115
00:04:48,047 --> 00:04:49,798
[Laughs maniacally]

116
00:04:50,674 --> 00:04:52,509
Okay, let's talk.

117
00:04:52,551 --> 00:04:54,386
[Laughs maniacally]

118
00:04:54,428 --> 00:04:55,930
What do you want to talk about?

119
00:04:56,055 --> 00:04:57,806
Where did you come from?

120
00:04:57,932 --> 00:05:00,434
Why are you playing
this weird game with Finn?

121
00:05:00,559 --> 00:05:02,811
[Laughing maniacally]

122
00:05:05,522 --> 00:05:08,067
He's playing
Mr. Laughing Silent Guy.

123
00:05:08,150 --> 00:05:10,319
-[Green Knight laughs]
- Game's over, bro.

124
00:05:10,402 --> 00:05:15,199
[Laughs] The game isn't over
until I strike you.

125
00:05:15,282 --> 00:05:17,034
Hmm.

126
00:05:17,076 --> 00:05:19,036
Let's come up with
a better way to settle this,

127
00:05:19,078 --> 00:05:20,663
like reasonable late teens.

128
00:05:21,205 --> 00:05:22,414
I'm listening.

129
00:05:22,456 --> 00:05:25,459
Well, we've got everything
set up for party games.

130
00:05:25,584 --> 00:05:27,586
How about if I beat you
two out of three,

131
00:05:27,670 --> 00:05:29,338
you got to answer our questions.

132
00:05:29,421 --> 00:05:30,839
Psst! Nuh!

133
00:05:30,923 --> 00:05:33,342
And if I win...chop, chop.

134
00:05:33,425 --> 00:05:34,551
Deal.

135
00:05:34,593 --> 00:05:36,595
Wait, Finn, I think he's
plotting something --

136
00:05:36,679 --> 00:05:38,430
I-It's fine. I'm 17.
I'm hittin' my stride.

137
00:05:38,472 --> 00:05:39,431
[Beeps]

138
00:05:43,185 --> 00:05:45,354
Hey, Green Knight,
why are they all mimey?

139
00:05:45,479 --> 00:05:47,106
Ah, just to keep things fair.

140
00:05:47,189 --> 00:05:50,067
[Clanking]

141
00:05:50,109 --> 00:05:52,111
[Sighs]
I don't think he can hear us.

142
00:05:52,194 --> 00:05:53,362
[Laughs sinisterly]

143
00:05:54,196 --> 00:05:55,364
Okay, guy.

144
00:05:55,489 --> 00:05:57,116
Why don't we start with
something basic

145
00:05:57,199 --> 00:06:00,202
like...balls and coconuts.

146
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:02,246
Hup! Hup!

147
00:06:02,329 --> 00:06:04,206
Hup, hup, hup, hup
hup, hup, hup.

148
00:06:04,248 --> 00:06:05,249
[Clank]

149
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,710
Ba-ba-ba-boom!

150
00:06:10,587 --> 00:06:11,255
Boom!

151
00:06:12,715 --> 00:06:14,717
- Okay, Finn!
- Yeah, yeah!

152
00:06:14,758 --> 00:06:16,760
- You got it, Finn!
- You go, boy!

153
00:06:19,763 --> 00:06:21,098
FINN:
[Slow-mo] Boooooooom!

154
00:06:24,018 --> 00:06:25,477
[Belches in slow-mo]

155
00:06:28,147 --> 00:06:28,856
[Tap]

156
00:06:29,523 --> 00:06:30,858
[Normal voice] Aw, what?

157
00:06:30,899 --> 00:06:34,403
I'll let you have that one,
'‘cause I'm a big boy today.

158
00:06:34,528 --> 00:06:37,156
But let's see you try and beat
four out of five, huh?

159
00:06:37,239 --> 00:06:39,241
[Whirring]

160
00:06:52,421 --> 00:06:54,548
How do you like them coconuts?

161
00:06:54,548 --> 00:06:56,884
I hate them coconuts.

162
00:06:56,925 --> 00:06:58,552
Somethings wrong.

163
00:06:58,552 --> 00:07:00,679
Yeah, I swear that looked fake.

164
00:07:00,763 --> 00:07:02,306
It was.

165
00:07:04,058 --> 00:07:06,185
I saw it all with
my Huntress vision.

166
00:07:19,948 --> 00:07:21,825
Finn is totally getting played.

167
00:07:22,576 --> 00:07:24,411
[Inhales]
All right.

168
00:07:24,953 --> 00:07:26,705
You got a freaky curveball, man.

169
00:07:27,456 --> 00:07:29,333
But can you climb a greasy pole?

170
00:07:31,460 --> 00:07:33,295
A greasy pole?!

171
00:07:33,337 --> 00:07:35,589
It's hard enough climbing
a non-greasy pole!

172
00:07:37,049 --> 00:07:39,718
Ready?
-[Chuckles] Mm-hmm!

173
00:07:40,594 --> 00:07:41,720
[Speaks quickly]
One, two, three, go!

174
00:07:44,098 --> 00:07:45,557
[Grunts]

175
00:07:48,477 --> 00:07:49,478
Ha, ha!

176
00:07:49,603 --> 00:07:52,731
-[Panting]
-[Slow clapping in distance]

177
00:07:52,815 --> 00:07:54,108
-[Normal voice] Huh?
-[Slow clap]

178
00:07:56,485 --> 00:07:58,737
Finn, you climb so good.

179
00:07:58,821 --> 00:08:01,198
I guess you win this round.

180
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:02,491
Hmm.

181
00:08:02,574 --> 00:08:03,617
Yay, Finn!

182
00:08:03,742 --> 00:08:05,369
- Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!
- That's right!

183
00:08:05,452 --> 00:08:07,496
- Yay, yay!
- What, what?

184
00:08:07,621 --> 00:08:09,331
Now's our chance, BMO.

185
00:08:09,373 --> 00:08:10,874
Is -- Is Finn gonna be okay?

186
00:08:10,874 --> 00:08:12,876
He's got this.
He's 17.

187
00:08:13,627 --> 00:08:15,129
Who's the ma-a-a-n?

188
00:08:15,129 --> 00:08:18,006
Who's the 17-year-old
ma-a-a-a-n?

189
00:08:18,006 --> 00:08:19,216
Hoo!

190
00:08:19,758 --> 00:08:20,634
You've been a good sport,

191
00:08:20,634 --> 00:08:22,761
so I'll let you
choose the tiebreaker.

192
00:08:23,512 --> 00:08:24,471
[Muffled] Don't do it!

193
00:08:24,513 --> 00:08:26,515
- Wait, don't do it!
- Not a good idea!

194
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:29,893
Very well. Hmm...

195
00:08:29,977 --> 00:08:33,439
How about a game of some good
old-fashioned arm wrestling?

196
00:08:33,522 --> 00:08:35,190
Arm wrestling, huh?

197
00:08:35,190 --> 00:08:36,567
I see what you did there.

198
00:08:36,650 --> 00:08:38,819
My guns are obviously
weak as heck

199
00:08:38,819 --> 00:08:40,320
from climbing that greasy pole.

200
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:42,406
If only I had some kind of...

201
00:08:42,448 --> 00:08:44,908
-[Whirs]
-...superhuman robot arm.

202
00:08:45,659 --> 00:08:46,702
Bam!

203
00:08:51,165 --> 00:08:52,207
BOTH:
Three, two, one, go!

204
00:08:52,332 --> 00:08:53,709
[Strained grunts]

205
00:08:56,086 --> 00:08:57,212
[Strained] Ahh!

206
00:08:57,337 --> 00:09:01,300
You can't tell from my face,
but I am smiling triumphantly.

207
00:09:01,341 --> 00:09:03,343
Nooo!

208
00:09:03,343 --> 00:09:06,472
It's...my...birthday!

209
00:09:06,555 --> 00:09:08,348
I know.

210
00:09:08,474 --> 00:09:10,434
It's my birthday, too.

211
00:09:10,476 --> 00:09:11,977
Fern?

212
00:09:15,606 --> 00:09:17,232
- Oh, no!
- No! Finn!

213
00:09:17,316 --> 00:09:19,109
[Shing!]

214
00:09:19,193 --> 00:09:20,694
[Fern chuckles]

215
00:09:20,736 --> 00:09:23,447
Finally, I win!

216
00:09:23,489 --> 00:09:24,823
-[Beeps]
- UNCLE GUMBALD: Fern!

217
00:09:25,949 --> 00:09:27,493
We've seen enough.

218
00:09:28,368 --> 00:09:30,621
[Beep, whoosh]

219
00:09:30,746 --> 00:09:32,372
-[Groans]
- Finn! Finn!

220
00:09:32,456 --> 00:09:33,457
Finn, are you all right?

221
00:09:33,499 --> 00:09:35,083
STARCHY:
I love you, Finn!

222
00:09:35,125 --> 00:09:37,002
Quick, eat this elk's heart.

223
00:09:37,085 --> 00:09:38,879
What is this?

224
00:09:41,590 --> 00:09:43,717
It's a family reunion.

225
00:09:44,343 --> 00:09:47,971
Uncle Gumbald, Cousin Chicle,
Aunt Lolly.

226
00:09:48,013 --> 00:09:49,973
How are you back?!

227
00:09:50,015 --> 00:09:51,350
Here's a hint.

228
00:09:51,391 --> 00:09:52,768
[As LSP] "Oh, my Glob."

229
00:09:54,144 --> 00:09:56,480
Lumpy Space Princess.

230
00:09:57,397 --> 00:09:59,775
[Whoosh]

231
00:10:02,236 --> 00:10:06,406
When she reset Ooo,
she reset...you.

232
00:10:07,407 --> 00:10:10,994
For 800 years, you kept us
imprisoned, Princezzin.

233
00:10:11,036 --> 00:10:14,248
No, you were happier
as candy people.

234
00:10:14,790 --> 00:10:16,375
We thought we were.

235
00:10:16,416 --> 00:10:17,668
But don't worry.

236
00:10:17,751 --> 00:10:20,254
It's your turn to be happy now.

237
00:10:20,295 --> 00:10:22,130
Get juiced.

238
00:10:22,172 --> 00:10:24,675
[Hisses]
Back off, gumwad!

239
00:10:24,675 --> 00:10:27,678
The vampire girl
is legitimately scary.

240
00:10:27,761 --> 00:10:28,679
Very well.

241
00:10:28,679 --> 00:10:30,806
You've withessed
our superior technology

242
00:10:30,889 --> 00:10:33,392
and watched
your champion crushed.

243
00:10:33,433 --> 00:10:34,184
[Vomits]

244
00:10:34,309 --> 00:10:37,563
We'll go...for now.

245
00:10:39,940 --> 00:10:42,025
[Laughs]

246
00:10:42,943 --> 00:10:45,904
This is my worst B-day ever.

247
00:10:45,946 --> 00:10:50,075
BMO AND JAKE: & Happy birthday to you &

248
00:10:50,075 --> 00:10:53,704
ALL: s Happy birthday to you J

249
00:10:53,829 --> 00:10:56,039
J Happy birthday... &

250
00:10:56,039 --> 00:10:58,709
& Mr. Finn Mart-ens J

251
00:10:58,834 --> 00:11:05,299
J Happy birthday to you 7

252
00:11:07,706 --> 00:11:11,918
s Come along with me J

253
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:16,172
J And the butterflies and bees &

254
00:11:18,967 --> 00:11:21,344
This party is so crazy!

